headline: The Clock Is Ticking on Starbucks’ Turnaround. Watch Sales and Margins.
summary: Starbucks’  coming earnings report and investor day are shaping up as a test of the narrative that CEO Brian Niccol is turning the company around.  The risk is that investors will lose patience, given the chain’s modest momentum in the U.S., lingering uncertainty in China, and a valuation that leaves little room for missteps.  In the 16 months since Niccol took the helm, Starbucks has taken meaningful steps to reshape the business, from management changes and cost cuts to store closures, investments in labor, and updates to the menu.

headline: Starbucks Beefs Up CEO Security Spending
summary: Starbucks has hiked its spending on security for Chief Executive Brian Niccol, saying his profile has risen and the “threat landscape” has become more concerning.  The coffee chain spent around $1.1 million on security for Niccol in the fiscal year ended Sept. 28.  Security spending was about $128,000 in the prior year, when Niccol started in the role.
